# Architecture Rules

## Layer Boundaries

| Layer | Can Import | Must NOT Import |
|-------|------------|-----------------|
| **Surfaces (UI)** | `hooks`, `di`, `ui`, `theme`, `types`, `navigation` | `core`, `persistence`, `domain/repository`, `infrastructure` |
| **Hooks** | `di`, `infrastructure` (WidgetSync only for sync calls) | `core` directly for business logic |
| **Use Cases** | `domain/repository` (interfaces), `types` | `persistence`, `core` (repos call core) |
| **Repositories** | `core`, `persistence`, `types` | React, UI |
| **Core** | Nothing (pure TS) | React, storage, I/O |

## SSOT (Single Source of Truth)

- **Time/profile data**: `TimeRepository` (via `MmkvTimeRepository`) — only place that reads/writes user/time to MMKV
- **Widget cache**: `TimeRepository.getWidgetCache()` — same time logic as `getTimeState()`
- **Progress colors**: `theme/progressColor.ts` — `getProgressColor(progress)`; UI consumes, no duplicate logic
- **Types/DTOs**: `types/index.ts` — `WidgetCache`, `UserProfile`, `TimeProgress`, etc.
- **Storage keys**: `persistence/schema.ts` — shared with native widgets

## Composition Root

- All repository → use case wiring in `di.ts`
- Add new use case: implement in `domain/useCases/`, instantiate in `di.ts`, export

## Data Flow

1. **Read**: Screen → Hook → Use Case → Repository → MMKV / Core
2. **Write**: Screen → Hook → Use Case → Repository.setX() → MMKV → subscribe() notifies
3. **Widget sync**: `syncWidgetCache()` calls `SyncWidgetUseCase.execute()` → `TimeRepository.getWidgetCache()` → MMKV → native bridge
